  "prompt": "Do you stop growing in height if you use the gym extensively?",
  "response": "No, using the gym does not stop height growth. Height is primarily determined by genetics and hormones, particularly during puberty. Strength training and exercise do not stunt growth as was once believed. In fact, regular exercise can be beneficial for overall physical development. \n\nFactors that influence height include:\n1. Genetics\n2. Nutrition\n3. Hormones (especially during puberty)\n4. Overall health\n\nIf you're still in your growth years (typically until late teens/early 20s), working out can actually support healthy growth and development. However, it's always best to consult with a healthcare professional or a qualified trainer about appropriate exercise routines for your age and development stage.",
